Command	Description
ls	List files and directories
cd	Change directory
pwd	Print working directory
mkdir <directory_name>	Create a new directory
rm <file_name>	Remove a file
rmdir <directory_name>	Remove an empty directory
mv <source> <destination>	Move or rename a file or directory
cp <source> <destination>	Copy a file or directory

Command	Description
cat <file_name>	Display the contents of a file
head <file_name>	Display the first few lines of a file
tail <file_name>	Display the last few lines of a file
less <file_name>	View a file page by page
grep <pattern> <file_name>	Search for a pattern in a file
wc -l <file_name>	Count the number of lines in a file
wc -w <file_name>	Count the number of words in a file
wc -c <file_name>	Count the number of characters in a file

Command	Description
nano <file_name>	Simple text editor
vim <file_name>	Powerful text editor
sed	Stream editor for text manipulation
awk	Text processing language

Command	Description
useradd <username>	Create a new user
passwd <username>	Change a user's password
userdel <username>	Delete a user
sudo	Execute commands with root privileges

Command	Description
ps	List running processes
kill <process_id>	Kill a process
top	Display system processes
htop	Interactive process viewer

Command	Description
ifconfig	Display network interface information
ping <hostname>	Send ping packets to a host
ssh <username>@<hostname>	Log into a remote machine via SSH
scp <source> <destination>	Copy files securely over SSH

Command	Description (Debian/Ubuntu)	Description (Fedora/CentOS)
apt	Package manager	yum
apt-get update	Update package lists	yum update
apt-get install <package_name>	Install a package	yum install <package_name>
apt-get remove <package_name>	Remove a package	yum remove <package_name>

# Linux Cheat Sheet

**Basic Commands**

| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `ls` | List files and directories |
| `cd` | Change directory |
| `pwd` | Print working directory |
| `mkdir <directory_name>` | Create a new directory |
| `rm <file_name>` | Remove a file |
| `rmdir <directory_name>` | Remove an empty directory |
| `mv <source> <destination>` | Move or rename a file or directory |
| `cp <source> <destination>` | Copy a file or directory |

**File Management**

| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `cat <file_name>` | Display the contents of a file |
| `head <file_name>` | Display the first few lines of a file |
| `tail <file_name>` | Display the last few lines of a file |
| `less <file_name>` | View a file page by page |
| `grep <pattern> <file_name>` | Search for a pattern in a file |
| `wc -l <file_name>` | Count the number of lines in a file |
| `wc -w <file_name>` | Count the number of words in a file |
| `wc -c <file_name>` | Count the number of characters in a file |

**Text Editing**

| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `nano <file_name>` | Simple text editor |
| `vim <file_name>` | Powerful text editor |
| `sed` | Stream editor for text manipulation |
| `awk` | Text processing language |

**User Management**

| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `useradd <username>` | Create a new user |
| `passwd <username>` | Change a user's password |
| `userdel <username>` | Delete a user |
| `sudo` | Execute commands with root privileges |

**Process Management**

| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `ps` | List running processes |
| `kill <process_id>` | Kill a process |
| `top` | Display system processes |
| `htop` | Interactive process viewer |

**Networking**

| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `ifconfig` | Display network interface information |
| `ping <hostname>` | Send ping packets to a host |
| `ssh <username>@<hostname>` | Log into a remote machine via SSH |
| `scp <source> <destination>` | Copy files securely over SSH |

**Package Management**

| Command | Description (Debian/Ubuntu) | Description (Fedora/CentOS) |
|---|---|---|
| `apt` | Package manager | `yum` | Package manager |
| `apt-get update` | Update package lists | `yum update` | Update package lists |
| `apt-get install <package_name>` | Install a package | `yum install <package_name>` | Install a package |
| `apt-get remove <package_name>` | Remove a package | `yum remove <package_name>` | Remove a package |

**Remember to adapt this cheat sheet to your specific Linux distribution and needs. You can customize it further by adding more commands and tips.**
